Section Header:
The Quick Links panel has multiple sections, each with a blue header bar and one or more links within that header. You will build the Quick Links panel using repeating instances of this REDCap form. For each section, define (1) the header for that section (what text should appear in the blue bar), (2) the order of that section among all sections, and (3) the decorative icon that should appear to the left of the text.

Once you've defined the Quick Links Section Header, you can enter up to 10 Quick Links per section by specifying (1) the text of the link, (2) the URL the link should go to, and (3) if the link should open in this same tab or a new tab.

Field Label:
Order for Quick Links Section

Numeric responses only. Decimals can be used to move one section between two existing sections.

Section Icon

These FontAwesome 4 Icons will place an icon at the start of each section header.
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, fa-cogs | 2, fa-database | 3, fa-globe | 4, fa-map-marker | 5, fa-star | 6, fa-comment | 7, fa-bug | 8, fa-info
